GUILTY plea entered to count 1, possess heroin - 2nd or subsquent offense.  Convicted.
The State moves to dismiss and read in counts 2 and 3.  Motion granted.
Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for two (2) years.
Conditions of probation:
1) Defendant is to comply with his ATR treatment that he is currently involved in;
2) AODA assessment and follow through;
3) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
4) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
5) Maintain fulltime employment/schooling/job search;
6) Pay court costs;
7) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
8) maintain absolute sobriety.
Minutes.
